  "texts": [
    "Thus one might conjecture that any compactly supported metric k-current in R d with finite flat norm is a flat chain.",
    "We shall refer to this conjecture as FCC F F (L)[k, d], the letters F F standing for \"finite flat\".",
    "It is natural to expect that FCC F F (L)[k, d] would be very closely related to FCC(AK)[k, d], however, except for the obvious implication, we are not able to assert any general relationship between the two conjectures.",
    "The exception to this is the top dimensional case k = d, where the flat norm coincides with the mass norm, and therefore FCC F F (L) [d, d] is obviously equivalent to FCC(AK) [d, d] and they both hold due to DePhilippis and Rindler [20].",
    "Structure of the paperThe paper is structured as follows."
  ],
